post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_43740520_43740728_3": {"length": 16, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 367}}, "n3337": {"so_43740520_43740728_3": {"length": 16, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 356}}, "n4659": {"so_43740520_43740728_3": {"length": 16, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 379}}}, "43740520": {"ViewCount": "106", "Body": "<p>Is it possible to create a thread with a function pointer to a class constructor?</p>\n<p>If this is possible, when would the class destructor get called?</p>\n<p>I have made this example of what i am looking for:</p>\n<pre><code>class ClassA\n{\npublic:\n    ClassA(void* argPtr)\n    { ... }\n};\n\nint main(void)\n{\n    pthread_t thread;\n    pthread_create(&amp;thread, NULL, &amp;ClassA(), NULL);\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "43740728", "Title": "Create thread via class constructor", "CreationDate": "2017-05-02T14:31:00.140", "Id": "43740520", "CommentCount": "4", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-02T14:40:36.033", "Score": "-1", "OwnerUserId": "4755799", "Tags": "<c++><multithreading><class><constructor><pthreads>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "43740728": {"Id": "43740728", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>Constructors are classified as \"special member functions\", and it is not possible to get a pointer to constructor function because it does not have a name (note that you are using class name, not a constructor function name, to invoke it):</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_43740520_43740728_0\">12.1 Constructors [class.ctor]</p>\n<p id=\"so_43740520_43740728_1\">1\n  Constructors do not have names.</p>\n<p id=\"so_43740520_43740728_2\">...</p>\n<p id=\"so_43740520_43740728_3\">2\n  A constructor is used to initialize objects of its class type. Because constructors do not have names, they are never found during name lookup;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Also <code>pthread_create</code> takes a pointer to a regular function, not to a member function.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2017-05-02T14:40:36.033", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2017-05-02T14:40:36.033", "ParentId": "43740520", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "7860670"}});